<text top="1215" left="32" width="544" height="51" font="font12" id="p1_t36" reading_order_no="38" segment_no="8" tag_type="text">nancy  forced  their  marriage  and </text>
<text top="1258" left="32" width="547" height="51" font="font12" id="p1_t37" reading_order_no="39" segment_no="8" tag_type="text">young  Will  fled  the  misery  of </text>
<text top="1302" left="32" width="544" height="50" font="font13" id="p1_t38" reading_order_no="40" segment_no="8" tag_type="text">Stratford-upon-Avon  for  London, </text>
<text top="1347" left="32" width="544" height="49" font="font14" id="p1_t39" reading_order_no="41" segment_no="8" tag_type="text">where  he  promptly  became  the </text>
<text top="1391" left="31" width="545" height="49" font="font14" id="p1_t40" reading_order_no="42" segment_no="8" tag_type="text">world’s  greatest  playwright.  Citing </text>
<text top="1434" left="32" width="544" height="50" font="font13" id="p1_t41" reading_order_no="43" segment_no="8" tag_type="text">the  omission  of  Anne’s  name  from </text>
<text top="1478" left="32" width="545" height="50" font="font13" id="p1_t42" reading_order_no="44" segment_no="8" tag_type="text">his  will,  academics  have  happily </text>
